Cicero himself never edited or collected his letters. But even in his lifetime there was some such project formed. The well-known locus classicus on the subject is Att. xvi. 5, 5, mearum epistularum nulla est συν- αγωγή, sed habel Tio-o instar septaaqinta. Ec quidem sunt a te quaedam sumendae.
